        "trailText":"World featherweight title contender, who announced he was gay last year, pops question to partner José Manuel on Facebook",
        "headline":"Boxer Orlando Cruz to marry his boyfriend",
        "body":"<p>The first openly gay male professional boxer has proposed to his partner in a film posted on Facebook.</p><p>Orlando Cruz, who made headlines when he came out last October, delighted followers with a video lasting about two minutes in which he asked his long-term boyfriend, José Manuel, to marry him.</p><p>Speaking in Spanish, the Puerto Rican featherweight fighter, 32, said: \"Through the ups and downs we've had, you've always been there for [me].</p><p>\"I'm a little bit nervous, but that aside, I want to tell you and share with your friends and my friends that if you want to marry me?</p><p>\"I want to share my life with you and want to be with you always, and support you 100%, and you support me 100%. I like you a lot, I love you and I look forward to your answer.\"</p><p>Cruz didn't have to wait long. Manuel accepted his proposal with his own emotional video, also posted on Facebook.</p><p>\"I want to tell you, yes, I do accept and would like to marry you, because I love you,\" he replied tearily. \"I'm a bit emotional. I didn't expect to find your proposal posted to Facebook.\"</p><p>Both videos have since been removed from the website.</p><p>Cruz also mentioned the proposal on his Twitter account, saying that he had taken an important step in his life and that he wants happiness for him and his partner as a couple.</p><p>Pedro Julio Serrano, spokesman for the US-based National Gay and Lesbian Task Force, said he will serve as the godfather at the couple's wedding.</p><p>However, it was unclear where the wedding would take place. Same-sex marriage is not allowed in Puerto Rico, or in Florida, where Cruz has a home.</p><p>Cruz is preparing to fight Orlando Salido for the world featherweight title in Las Vegas this October – a year on from his public announcement that he is a \"proud gay man\".</p><!-- Guardian Watermark: internal-code/content/415124692|2013-10-07T10:05:57Z|3a76e61ccf18f7859bd58ec381afe1b4d6e84c4e -->",
